PARLIAMENT - The National Assembly adopted parliament s ad hoc committee report on the SABC board's fitness to hold office. All parties involved adopted the report, except for the UDM who raised an objection because Hlaudi Motsoeneng was not given an opportunity to make submissions before the committee.The report recommends criminal charges against witnesses who misled Parliament or gave false evidence.It also calls for Communications Minister Faith Muthambi to appear before the Ethics Committee.READ: MPs set sights on appointing interim SABC boardParliament will now send the report to President Jacob Zuma for his consideration.eNCA